Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: San Francisco
Description: San Francisco, in northern California, is a hilly city on the tip of a peninsula surrounded by the Pacific Ocean and San Francisco Bay. It's known for its year-round fog, iconic Golden Gate Bridge, cable cars and colorful Victorian houses. Home to the most notorious prison, Alcatraz Island.

Name: Knapps Castle
Description: An Old stone building now in ruins. You get a great view of the lower inland valley, especially the Chumash lake. Very easy hike/drive for a great view point of iconic Santa Barbara

Name: Disneyland
Description: Founded by Walt Disney, Disneyland Park is highly regarded as "The Happiest Place on Earth" and is full of thrills and excietment for all ages.

Name: Mt. Kilimanjaro
Description: Mt. Kilimanjaro is a dormant volcano in Tanzania. It is the highest mountain in Africa, with its summit about 4,900 metres from its base, and 5,895 metres above sea level.

Name: Cairo, Egypt
Description: The sixth most populous national capital in the world. Located on the Nile River,  the center of the city is home to Tahrir Square and the vast Egyptian Museum, a trove of antiquities including royal mummies and gilded King Tutankhamun artifacts.
